Privacy
‍
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose personal information when  you use our intermediary grocery delivery app "Dinna" (the "App"). We are committed  to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. You  consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy by using the App.
‍
1. Information We Collect
‍
1.1 Personal Information: When you sign up and use our App, we may collect certain  personal information, such as your name, email address, and delivery address. This  information is necessary for us to provide you with the requested services.
1.2 Usage Information: We may also collect usage information, including but not limited  to your interactions with the App, swipes, and preferences. This information helps us  improve the user experience and tailor the content to your interests.
‍
2. Use of Information
‍
2.1 Provide and Improve Services: We use the collected information to provide and  improve our App, personalize your experience, process your orders, and communicate  with you about your orders and account.
2.2 Analytics and Aggregated Data: We may use aggregated and anonymized data for  analytical purposes, such as understanding user trends, preferences, and demographics.  This data does not personally identify you.
2.3 Marketing Communications: With your consent, we may send you promotional  emails or push notifications about our services, offers, or other relevant information. You  can opt-out of these communications at any time by following the instructions provided  in the communication.
‍
3. Data Sharing and Disclosure
‍
3.1 Third-Party Services: We may share your personal information with trusted third party services, such as the grocery delivery services you select for checkout. This is  necessary to process and fulfill your orders.
3.2 Legal Requirements: We may disclose your personal information if required by law,  court order, or government regulation, or if we believe that such disclosure is necessary  to protect our rights, property, or safety, or the rights, property, or safety of others.
‍
4. Data Security
‍
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from  unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, please be aware that no method of  transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot  guarantee absolute security.
‍
5. Changes to the Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be  effective immediately upon posting the updated Privacy Policy in the App. Your  continued use of the App aYer the posting of the updated Privacy Policy constitutes your  acceptance of the changes.